# History: planning-unmerged-parent-contract-compile-smoke-gate

## v1.1.0 (2026-07-02)

Amended after a NOGO→R1 revision on ProjectOdyssey #5516 revealed that
**4-of-4** reviewer-flagged unverified APIs were WRONG on first `Read`:

1. `randn` — R0 assumed `mean=/std=` kwargs. On-disk
   (`src/projectodyssey/tensor/tensor_creation.mojo:531`) signature is
   `def randn(shape: List[Int], dtype: DType, seed: Int = 0) raises -> AnyTensor`
   — N(0,1) only. R0 test would not compile.
2. `cross_entropy` — R0 assumed integer class-index labels. On-disk
   (`src/projectodyssey/core/loss.mojo:260-292`) targets MUST be one-hot,
   same shape as logits. R0 would silently produce wrong loss (no dtype
   guard raise). Fix: `one_hot_encode` from
   `src/projectodyssey/data/formats/idx_loader.mojo:246`.
3. `AnyTensor.store[dtype]` — RIGHT (`any_tensor.mojo:1499`) but
   correct-by-coin-flip: `.set` also exists at line 860 with ~12
   dtype overloads.
4. `extract_batch_pair` — RIGHT
   (`src/projectodyssey/data/batch_utils.mojo:76-78` returns
   `Tuple[AnyTensor, AnyTensor]`) but unverified in R0.

Primary added learning: **When a reviewer NOGOs a plan for unverified
APIs, `Read` each flagged API's source line NOW and revise every
assumption that was wrong — do NOT add a "verify later" step to the
plan.** Assume 100% wrong-rate on cited-but-unread APIs until proven
otherwise on disk.

Sub-patterns added (all triggered from the same "planning revision
after NOGO for a Mojo/ProjectOdyssey issue" context):

- **Two-tier convergence assertion** — hard floor
  `assert_true(loss_final < loss_initial)` asserted BEFORE the
  issue-prescribed `< 0.95 * loss_initial` check, so failure logs
  distinguish "no decrease" from "insufficient decrease." Never
  weaken the issue-prescribed threshold; mitigate on data/hyperparams
  side (samples×3.2, class-mean bias×2, warm-up epoch).
- **Same-line coordination hazard on rebase** — when two concurrent
  PRs edit the identical line, rebase detects the pre-fixed line as
  an empty hunk; drop it with `git commit --amend --no-edit`, no
  merge conflict.
- **Cross-file caller grep before signature change** —
  `grep -rn 'fname(' --include='*.mojo'` to prove no other file
  calls the per-example function before changing its signature.
- **Smoke-run the example's own `main()`** — a test file that
  imports from the example proves compile but NOT that `main()`
  runs end-to-end (arg parser, dataset loader, checkpoint path
  can all break independently).
- **Name-collision with overload family trap** — `.set` (12 overloads,
  `any_tensor.mojo:860`) and `.store[dtype]` (parametric, line 1499)
  both exist on `AnyTensor`. Two-of-a-kind API names on the same
  type require explicit grep of BOTH forms before citation.

Failed-attempts table grew from 7 rows to 13 (added attempts 8-13
capturing the above patterns as concrete R0-vs-R1 misses).

## v1.0.0 (2026-07-02)

Initial capture from ProjectOdyssey issue #5516 plan review (parent
issue #5515 unmerged; only an approved-plan comment existed). Seven
learnings distilled from six unverified-API assumptions plus a
same-line-coordination hazard.

Merged in PR
[HomericIntelligence/ProjectMnemosyne#2935](https://github.com/HomericIntelligence/ProjectMnemosyne/pull/2935).
